DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: The most common type of kidney cancer. It begins in the lining of the renal tubules in the kidney. The renal tubules filter the blood and produce urine._This gene plays a role in transcriptional activation. It is involved in melanogenesis.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: Cancer that develops in the lining of the renal tubules, which filter the blood and produce urine.

Concepts.definition: A carcinoma arising from the renal parenchyma.  There is a strong correlation between cigarette smoking and the development of renal cell carcinoma.  The clinical presentation includes : hematuria, flank pain and a palpable lumbar mass.  A high percentage of renal cell carcinomas are diagnosed when an ultrasound is performed for other purposes.  Radical nephrectomy is the standard intervention procedure.  Renal cell carcinoma is generally considered to be resistant to radiation treatment and chemotherapy.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Human MALAT1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 11q13.1 and is approximately 9 kb in length. This allele, which encodes metastasis-associated lung adenocarcinoma transcript 1 non-coding RNA, may be involved in tumorigenesis. Aberrant expression of the gene is associated with non-small cell lung cancer and the gene may be involved in a translocation t(6;11)(p21.1;q13) with the human TFEB gene that may be associated with renal cell carcinoma.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Human ASPSCR1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17q25 and is approximately 40 kb in length. This allele, which encodes tether containing UBX domain for GLUT4 protein, plays a role in the regulation of insulin-mediated glucose transport. A chromosomal translocation t(X;17)(p11;q25) fuses the gene to the TFE3 gene and is associated with alveolar soft part sarcomas.
